fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.design

Interface IThemedDesign

  • All Superinterfaces:
    IAttachable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IDashboardDesign, IDataDesign, IFormDesign, IListDesign, IPasswordAuthnDesign

    public interface IThemedDesign
extends IAttachable
    Base interface for pages that require templates for rendering and with which style sheets can be associated.

    Note: implementations are permitted to defer persistence of design configuration changes for up to a second, to efficiently store a batch of changes. If the design configuration is externally updated when changes are pending (for example, by modifying a configuration file) then the deferred changes will be lost.

    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    REFLEXE Technologies
    See Also:
    IThemedPage

      • getStyleSheets

        List<IStyleSheet> getStyleSheets()
        Gets the list of stylesheets for this page design. These should be compatible with the current template. Values in the list are returned in the order that they were added.

        Note: the returned list will only include objects that are currently available in the OSGi service registry and match the attachId and attachVersion (using a version range, if the version was non-null) at the time each stylesheet was added to the design configuration.

        Returns:
        the list of stylesheets, possibly empty, never null.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        getStyleSheetIds(), getStyleMedia(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes.IStyleSheet)

      • getStyleMedia

        String getStyleMedia(IStyleSheet styleSheet)
        Gets the optional media attribute associated with the specified stylesheet for this design, if defined.
        Parameters:
        styleSheet - one of the stylesheets returned by invoked the getStyleSheets() method on this design instance.
        Returns:
        the non-empty value of the media attribute (if defined) or null. With CSS2 (or more recent), this should be either a media query or a media type.

        See Also:

      • addStyleSheet

        void addStyleSheet(IStyleSheet styleSheet,
                   StyleMediaType... media)
            throws ConcurrentModificationException
        Adds a stylesheet for this page design. Should be compatible with the current template.

        If the stylesheet has already been added to this design, then adding it again will overwrite any previous value(s) defined for the media attribute.

        Parameters:
        styleSheet - the non-null stylesheet to add.
        media - optional CSS2 media type(s) to add to the page design, for example all, screen, or print. For designs with non-CSS styles, the media parameter can be omitted.
        Throws:
        ConcurrentModificationException - if the design configuration was externally updated when invoking this method.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        addStyleSheet(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes.IStyleSheet, CharSequence)

      • addStyleSheet

        void addStyleSheet(IStyleSheet styleSheet,
                   CharSequence mediaQuery)
            throws ConcurrentModificationException
        Adds a stylesheet for this page design, using CSS3 media query syntax. Should be compatible with the current template.

        If the stylesheet has already been added to this design, then adding it again will overwrite any previous value(s) defined for the media attribute.

        Parameters:
        styleSheet - the non-null stylesheet to add.
        mediaQuery - the CSS3 media query for conditional CSS file import, such as
        only screen and (min-device-width: 320px) and (max-device-width: 480px)
        (this example will not be interpreted in older browsers due to the "only" prefix). Syntax validation is not enforced.
        Throws:
        ConcurrentModificationException - if the design configuration was externally updated when invoking this method.
        Since:
        1.0
        See Also:
        addStyleSheet(fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes.IStyleSheet, fr.reflexe.viewshell.api.themes.StyleMediaType...)
